AB  - Currently, unmanned aerial vehicles UAVs (drones) are widely used to monitor the territory and objects located in the traffic zone. However, for regions with poorly developed communication infrastructure, there are problems associated with the transfer of information coming from UAV to Data Center. The article proposes to solve the problem with the help of a system based on the use of UAVs and a geostationary Earth satellite. Thanks to this approach, it is possible not only to monitor objects in the traffic zone, but also to transfer data to the processing center regardless of the state of telecommunications in this region. The presence of such an opportunity creates the prerequisites for the effective use of Big Data and Digital Twin technologies, which bring solutions in this area to a qualitatively higher level. To reduce the cost of the project and improve the technical characteristics, data processing should be carried out using Cloud and Edge computing.
